# GLM after nordic

## Overview
This folder contains the first-level GLM analysis performed on the post-NORDIC functional data in native EPI space.

## Purpose
The purpose of this step is to model task-related responses separately for run 1, run 2, and run 3 while preserving laminar specificity and avoiding unnecessary blurring across cortical depth.

## Processing strategy
The first-level GLM was fit separately for each run using the complete 4D post-NORDIC magnitude series. The model followed an SPM-style configuration with:
- canonical SPM HRF
- AR(1) noise model
- cosine drift terms
- high-pass filtering
- no spatial smoothing
- native-space fitting only

## Input data
The analysis used:
- the full 4D post-NORDIC magnitude image for each run
- event timing information stored as onset, duration, and trial type
- model settings consistent with the original workflow

## Why full 4D data were required
A single 3D image is not sufficient for GLM fitting. Therefore, the complete time series was used for each run so that task events could be modeled properly across time.

## Typical outputs
This folder may contain:
- design_matrix.csv
- events_runX_used.csv
- effect-size maps
- t-statistic maps
- z-score maps
- run-specific quality-control summaries

## Notes
Subfolders such as run1, run2, and run3 can be used to keep the outputs organized. Only final modeling outputs and related design files should be stored here.
